headline: Centene (CNC): Losses Rising 3.1% Annually, Investors Eye Path to Profitability
summary: Centene (CNC) remains unprofitable, with losses rising at a 3.1% annual rate over the last five years. However, the company is forecast to deliver EPS growth of 72.58% per year and is expected to return to profitability within three years. While revenue is only projected to grow 1.7% per year, significantly slower than the broader US market's 10.3% expectation, Centene’s low Price-to-Sales Ratio leaves it trading below estimated fair value.
